ncounters at the White House between Bill Clinton and Monica Lewinsky, a liaison that culminated in a stunning scandal and the spectacle of the president’s impeachment and trial. As Campbell demonstrates in this absorbing chronicle, 1995 was a year of extraordinary events, a watershed at the turn of the millennium. The effects of that pivotal year reverberate still, marking the close of one century and the dawning of another.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aNineteen ninety-five, A.D. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh  aamerican culture.  aamerican history.  aamerican politics.  aamerican presidency.  abeginning of the internet.  abill clinton.  abombing.  abosnian war.  adomestic terrorism.  adouble murder.  agovernment and governing.  ahigh profile case.  ahistory.  aimpeachment.  ainternational negotiations.  ainternet.  alate 20th century american history.  amainstream.  amonica lewinsky.  aoj simpson.  aoklahoma city bombing.  apolitical scandal.  apresident clinton.  aretrospective.  ascandal.  atrial of the century.  atrial.  aunited states of america.  aworld wide web.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052027399340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095971240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520959712423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520959712/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY